The paper deals with metrics and coding invariants, which are topics commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of algorithms and bounds suggests numerical analysis (cs.NA) as a possible sub-category. The study of linear isometries and canonical decompositions suggests the sub-category of symbolic computation (cs.SI). Finally, the discussion of the MacWilliams Identity and Extension Property suggests coding theory (cs.CC) as a possible sub-category.
